<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-08T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 165.102/284</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-08T19:00:00+01:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 8, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 9, 8 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>1036. Informed that one month’s supply of dyestuffs has been released for
                            the shipment by German authorities and that shipment was started for
                            Rotterdam yesterday. Shipment to be made on <hi rend="italic">Matanzas</hi> and is to be of about 2,200 tons, practically filling
                            steamer. Further release will be made of amount of dyes damaged on <hi rend="italic">Sun</hi> as soon as this amount is established. No
                            further release for any period until present shipment has been used
                            up.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GJW2">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>